    },
    {
      "block_id": "p42_b4",
      "translation": "In 2020, AIA successfully navigated the challenges brought by the COVID-19 pandemic. During this period, our top priority was ensuring the safety of our"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p42_b5",
      "translation": "employees while providing uninterrupted service to customers, agents and partners. Currently, our business has regained momentum, with the Group's new business value in the first two months of"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p42_b6",
      "translation": "2021 growing 15% compared to the same period in 2020. Given that containment measures restricted face-to-face sales activities, we accelerated the development and"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p42_b7",
      "translation": "adoption of online and remote sales tools. Currently, all AIA agents and bancassurance distribution channels can sell our products remotely."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p42_b8",
      "translation": "As movement restrictions eased, these tools supported sales momentum recovery across AIA's business markets."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p42_b9",
      "translation": "Distribution"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p42_b10",
      "translation": "On the agent channel, we continued to strengthen our \"best agents\" force, with double-digit growth in new agent and manager recruits supported by the shift to online recruitment and onboarding."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p42_b11",
      "translation": "During the pandemic, face-to-face meetings were restricted, resulting in a 28% decline in new business value in 2020. As restrictions eased and we adopted new digital tools, sales momentum recovered and continued into 2021. In the first two months, the agent channel"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p42_b12",
      "translation": "recorded very strong year-on-year growth in new business value."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p42_b13",
      "translation": "In 2020, new business value from partner distribution channels declined 41%, reflecting the impact of travel restrictions. From February 2020, these restrictions caused sales from mainland China visitors to Hong Kong to essentially halt. Excluding sales from mainland China visitors to Hong Kong, partner distribution new business value grew 5% in the second half of 2020 compared to the first half. In 2020, our bancassurance partners performed well, with Bangkok Bank Public Company Limited, Bank Central Asia (BCA) in Indonesia and Public Bank Berhad in Malaysia all recording year-on-year growth in new business value."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p42_b14",
      "translation": "Regional Markets"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p42_b15",
      "translation": "AIA's China business recorded strong momentum in 2021, with very robust growth in new business value in the first two months compared to the same period in 2020. 2020 new business value of USD 968 million declined 17% from 2019, primarily due to limited sales in the early first quarter when COVID-19 initially emerged. As movement restrictions eased, new business momentum improved rapidly. New business value resumed our typical seasonality pattern, with greater concentration in the first half. In 2020, AIA's China business contributed the largest share to the Group's new business value."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p42_b16",
      "translation": "Following travel restrictions, AIA's Hong Kong business saw sales from mainland China visitors essentially halt from early February 2020, resulting in a significant decline in new business value. New business value margin declined, reflecting underwriting expense overruns from reduced new business volume, product mix changes and the impact of lower interest rates. After-tax operating profit increased 10%. Macau resumed the Individual Visit Scheme for mainland China visitors in late September 2020. This supported sales recovery from mainland China visitors to Macau, accounting for over one-third of AIA Macau's annualized new premiums in the fourth quarter."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p42_b17",
      "translation": "AIA's Thailand business performed excellently in the second half, with new business value growing 33% compared to the first half. Although full-year new business value declined 4%, as movement restrictions eased in the second half, new business value recorded positive month-on-month growth."
